why is kimi k2 CONSTANTLY getting more and more expensive.. 

outputs were like 50 cents 2 months ago its 2$ now..

2 months ago we ran kimi with tiny context size for it to fit on h200 GPUs. Then we migrated it to run on b200s so as to have full context. Then, the new kimi was released (0905) which increased context size again from 131k to 202k, meaning the concurrency we can support per node was once again lowered meaning more cost per request.

We've had 2 price changes as far as I know, and we're still 20% cheaper on input and 5% cheaper on input then next cheapest on openrouter, and that is an fp4 quantized version which will have much lower quality. Beyond that one it's 0.6/2.50 input output.

import os

)
